  "prompt": "What is the average salary for an IT consultant in Dubai?",
  "response": "As of the most recent data available in 2023, the average salary for an IT consultant in Dubai typically ranges between **AED 180,000 to AED 300,000 per year** (approximately **$49,000 to $82,000 USD**). However, this can vary depending on factors such as:\n\n1. **Experience Level**:  \n   - Entry-level IT consultants may earn closer to **AED 120,000 to AED 180,000 per year**.  \n   - Mid-level professionals with 5\u201310 years of experience can expect **AED 200,000 to AED 300,000 per year**.  \n   - Senior consultants with extensive expertise and certifications can earn **AED 300,000 to AED 500,000+ per year**.\n\n2. **Industry and Employer**: Consulting firms, multinational corporations, and tech-focused industries often offer higher salaries compared to smaller companies.\n\n3. **Specialization**: IT consultants with expertise in high-demand areas like cloud computing, cybersecurity, AI, or ERP systems (e.g., SAP, Oracle) may command higher salaries.\n\n4. **Certifications**: Holding advanced certifications (e.g., PMP, ITIL, AWS, CISSP) can significantly boost earning potential.\n\nIt's important to note that salaries in Dubai are often tax-free, making the take-home pay more attractive compared to many other regions. Always check updated job postings or salary surveys for the most accurate and current information.",
